Docker packages an application along with its libraries and dependencies into a container.
Containers ensure that applications run consistently across development, testing, and production environments.
Docker is lightweight and uses fewer resources compared to traditional virtual machines.
It helps developers deploy applications quickly and efficiently.
Docker is widely used in DevOps, cloud computing, and microservices architectures.
Docker images are used to create containers, and these images can be shared through repositories.
It supports Linux, Windows, and various cloud platforms.
